===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} [[w:Morpheus (mythology)|Morpheus]] the god of [[dream]]s.

===Noun===
'''morphine'''
{{wikipedia}}
#A [[crystalline]] [[alkaloid]] (7,8-didehydro-4,5-epoxy-
17-methyl-morphinan-3,6-diol), extracted from [[opium]], the [[salt]]s of which are [[soluble]] in [[water]] and are used as [[analgesic]]s, [[anaesthetic]]s and [[sedative]]s.

